@NODE "Errors"
@TITLE "Errormessages"
@NEXT "Appendices.guide/HistoryLog"
@PREV "Libraries.guide/Libraries"
@TOC "Manual.guide/Main"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------------------- Errormessages -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Main" "Errormessages"
@{U}11) Errormessages@{UU}

   If an error occures while  parsing your input, evaluation an  expression...
Laplace returns a short message, which gives you a simple explanation of  what
went wrong. Together with this message comes an error number which consists of
four digits. The first digit is the number of the group to which the error be-
longs. The following three digits are a consecutive number for the error  mes-
sage.

   These are the groups, indicated by the first digit:

 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}1@{UB} - syntax errors, like forgotten brackets.
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}2@{UB} - mathmatical error, e.g. division by zero.
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}3@{UB} - file access errors.
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}4@{UB} - reference errors, like undefined references.
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}5@{UB} - error of external modules.
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}9@{UB} - errors that don't belong to another group.

   Finally, here is the list of all error codes:

   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1000"}  1000 - @{I}Syntax error. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1001"}  1001 - @{I}Unexpected characters following expression. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1002"}  1002 - @{I}Missing close bracket. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1003"}  1003 - @{I}Too many closing brackets. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1004"}  1004 - @{I}Expected an opening bracket at this place. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1005"}  1005 - @{I}Unterminated string. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1006"}  1006 - @{I}Unterminated comment. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1007"}  1007 - @{I}Unexpected character. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1008"}  1008 - @{I}Unexpected keyword. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1009"}  1009 - @{I}Unknown control character. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1010"}  1010 - @{I}Unknown option. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1011"}  1011 - @{I}'else' without if. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1012"}  1012 - @{I}... expects n argument(s). @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1013"}  1013 - @{I}'...' expects n argument(s). @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1014"}  1014 - @{I}'...' expects n argument(s). @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1015"}  1015 - @{I}'...' expects n..m argument(s). @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1016"}  1016 - @{I}Argument count mismatch. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1017"}  1017 - @{I}Expected argument. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1018"}  1018 - @{I}Invalid number. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1019"}  1019 - @{I}Index exceeds the valid range [n,m]. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1020"}  1020 - @{I}Expected index of order n. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1021"}  1021 - @{I}Option exceeds the valid range [n,m]. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1022"}  1022 - @{I}Expected function with one argument. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1023"}  1023 - @{I}Cannot use '...' as a constructor. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1024"}  1024 - @{I}Expected identifier with interval. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1025"}  1025 - @{I}Invalid interval. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1026"}  1026 - @{I}Reference doesn't expect arguments. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1027"}  1027 - @{I}Class '...' has no member '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1028"}  1028 - @{I}Unexpected 'void' result. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR1029"}  1029 - @{I}Constant reference must not have arguments. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2000"}  2000 - @{I}Division by zero. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2001"}  2001 - @{I}acos out of [-1,1]. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2002"}  2002 - @{I}asin out of [-1,1]. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2003"}  2003 - @{I}Factorial only defined for integers. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2004"}  2004 - @{I}Singularity of cot(). @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2005"}  2005 - @{I}Vector dimensions don't match. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2006"}  2006 - @{I}Matrix dimensions don't match. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2007"}  2007 - @{I}Matrix must be square. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2008"}  2008 - @{I}This matrix cannot be inverted. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2009"}  2009 - @{I}Operator '...' not defined for .... @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2010"}  2010 - @{I}Expected object of type '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR2011"}  2011 - @{I}Return type mismatch. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR3000"}  3000 - @{I}Read/write error on file '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR3001"}  3001 - @{I}Unable to open file '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR4000"}  4000 - @{I}Undefined reference '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR4001"}  4001 - @{I}Expected object of type '...' in reference '...', subexpression@{UI}
        @{I}'...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR4002"}  4002 - @{I}Type not supported in reference '...', subexpression '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR4003"}  4003 - @{I}Missing closing '`' character in '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR5000"}  5000 - @{I}Unable to load module '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR5001"}  5001 - @{I}Module '...' returned the error '...'. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR5002"}  5002 - @{I}In module '...': no argument '...' found. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR5003"}  5003 - @{I}In module '...': argument '...' has invalid type. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR5004"}  5004 - @{I}Handle doesn't point to an opened module. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR9000"}  9000 - @{I}Out of memory. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR9001"}  9001 - @{I}This function is not implemented yet. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR9002"}  9002 - @{I}User break. @{UI}
   @{" * " LINK "ERROR9003"}  9003 - @{I}Internal error. @{UI}







